The Conservative Party is currently pulled between a stronger populist current that prioritises popular sovereignty and national interest of living citizens, and residual institutional, economic-liberal, and socially conservative currents. The populist direction has gained ground, but the party as a whole still retains more institutional and competence language than Reform UK or Restore Britain.

